1
00:00:04,804 --> 00:00:06,038
Social media is flooded

2
00:00:06,039 --> 00:00:07,107
with these photos.

3
00:00:07,607 --> 00:00:08,975
What are you guys thinking?

4
00:00:10,910 --> 00:00:11,910
What?

5
00:00:12,145 --> 00:00:13,645
Look how well it's working.

6
00:00:13,646 --> 00:00:14,914
It's got real buzz.

7
00:00:16,750 --> 00:00:17,450
Bai Xing's approach

8
00:00:17,451 --> 00:00:18,550
was a bit aggressive,

9
00:00:18,551 --> 00:00:19,119
but we can talk about it...

10
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:20,720
So you're the one who told him to do it.

11
00:00:21,755 --> 00:00:22,989
Why are you acting like this?

12
00:00:23,490 --> 00:00:24,490
Like what?

13
00:00:31,965 --> 00:00:33,632
No press photos are to be posted yet.

14
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:34,267
Wait until we've reviewed the copy,

15
00:00:34,268 --> 00:00:35,588
then we'll release them together.

16
00:00:37,137 --> 00:00:39,471
Exactly. Nothing goes out yet.

17
00:00:39,472 --> 00:00:40,940
Not until we've approved it.

18
00:00:45,712 --> 00:00:46,813
Why are you so upset too?

19
00:00:47,981 --> 00:00:49,782
This isn't the way to get famous.

20
00:00:49,783 --> 00:00:51,017
You need to know when to stop.

21
00:00:51,418 --> 00:00:53,219
Didn't you want the publicity?

22
00:00:54,421 --> 00:00:55,755
You're being weird.

23
00:00:56,189 --> 00:00:57,957
We have the traffic and the hype.

24
00:00:58,224 --> 00:00:59,592
What's your problem?

25
00:01:00,326 --> 00:01:01,227
Traffic is

26
00:01:01,228 --> 00:01:02,928
a double-edged sword.

27
00:01:02,929 --> 00:01:04,263
Doing that in front of the media...

28
00:01:04,264 --> 00:01:05,764
how do you expect them
to handle the story?

29
00:01:07,167 --> 00:01:08,902
We're from different agencies,

30
00:01:09,302 --> 00:01:11,036
but our fanbases overlap.

31
00:01:11,037 --> 00:01:12,597
We're competing for the same resources.

32
00:01:12,839 --> 00:01:14,907
Just worry about yourself.

33
00:01:14,908 --> 00:01:16,309
We both get what we need.

34
00:01:16,643 --> 00:01:17,643
Wasn't that

35
00:01:17,744 --> 00:01:18,344
why you brought me

36
00:01:18,345 --> 00:01:19,345
onto this project?

37
00:01:19,346 --> 00:01:20,346
Of course not.

38
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:29,155
Then what was your goal?

39
00:01:36,229 --> 00:01:37,229
Tell me.

40
00:01:38,064 --> 00:01:39,766
Baili Foundation Number Five.

41
00:01:40,667 --> 00:01:41,667
BY.

42
00:01:42,635 --> 00:01:43,635
Is that you?

43
00:01:44,204 --> 00:01:45,204
If it's not,

44
00:01:45,572 --> 00:01:46,873
then I'm just losing my mind.

45
00:01:56,249 --> 00:01:57,249
Fine.

46
00:01:58,918 --> 00:02:00,587
Since I'm kept in the dark anyway.

47
00:02:11,931 --> 00:02:12,931
Clearly,

48
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,935
you have no intention
of telling me anything.

49
00:02:58,945 --> 00:03:01,814
You followed me all the
way back, and for what?

50
00:03:03,216 --> 00:03:04,484
You won't speak when I ask,

51
00:03:04,817 --> 00:03:06,177
and you won't answer my questions.

52
00:03:09,956 --> 00:03:11,391
My patience is wearing thin.

53
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:13,426
I'm done wasting time.

54
00:03:15,061 --> 00:03:16,195
I'm opening the door now.

55
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:17,997
If you are BY,

56
00:03:18,731 --> 00:03:19,766
then come in.

57
00:03:20,633 --> 00:03:21,633
If not,

58
00:03:23,336 --> 00:03:24,370
then get lost.
